{
  "stem": "5810.4",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I don't know what my feelings would be, I don't know what my emotions will make me do, but I don't think it was a good idea.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they felt the same way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So I did not go to Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But then came another, another situation, which is like the world goes around.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "During a, a bombing in Belgium by the allied forces, it was actually the American bombing, when I ran for shelter under a doorway I fell and I had broken my front tooth.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that stayed with me, of course, through the war and after the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And while I was in the army the front tooth started to react, the nerves started to react, and it started to darken and become black.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And just as a-- as a funny little story, is that the, the thing that the American soldiers, or I should say the American Air Force, had done and broken, the American army fixed for me.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I'm only saying that because while I was sitting there explaining it to the dentist, who was an officer, I told them, well, it took you about 20 years, but you're fixing something that you people did to me.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then, of course, he was interested in the story and I went on from there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But what happened just when I was about to be discharged in the army, it was 1958, and the Lebanese conflict happened with Israel and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I was-- I had an [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "MOS, ?] a job in the army that was very, very tough to do and tough to get.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And about a week before I was to be discharged, my company and what I was doing was necessary in Lebanon, in case the conflict expanded.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
